{
  "$comment": "BIH theme-token catalog — THE single source of truth for every color used by the investigation graph, the app chrome, the SidePanel, the Settings/customize UI, and the report. Consumed two ways from this one file: frontend/src/theme/theme.ts (Cytoscape stylesheet + CSS vars for the app/SidePanel) and backend/app/theme.py (the report's :root CSS custom properties + its inlined Cytoscape style). Each token keeps a stable {id, label, category} and carries a per-theme `values` map. THEME KEYS: `neo-tokyo-night` (the editable Custom base), `dark` (locked modern-slate), `light` (locked modern-clean), and `print-light` (the report/exhibit palette, ALWAYS used for printed/exported case files regardless of the canvas theme). CANVAS PRESETS (P6, `canvasPresets`): `custom` -> base `neo-tokyo-night` + user overrides (the only editable preset), `dark` -> base `dark` (locked), `light` -> base `light` (locked). The report NEVER follows the canvas theme — it resolves print-light so case files stay paper-legible. Token id -> CSS var is mechanical: '--bih-' + id with dots->dashes (node.address.fill -> --bih-node-address-fill). neon is reserved for meaning and the semantic channels stay mutually distinct under every theme (risk / entity / fifo-trace / value / annotation / seed never collide) with non-color cues (badge, star, dashed conventions, node shapes) carrying meaning too for color-blind safety.",
